HSBC Names Sean O’Sullivan Group Chief Operating Officer

-- B y   H o w a r d   M u s t o e
-- 
2011-07-29T16:27:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-29/hsbc-names-o-sullivan-chief-operating-officer-1-.html
HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA) , Europe’s biggest
bank by market value, promoted Sean O’Sullivan to become group
chief operating officer.  O’Sullivan, 55, will take up the new job next month and
report to Chief Executive Officer  Stuart Gulliver , the London-
based bank said in a statement today. He joined HSBC in 1980.  He had been group chief technology and services officer
since January, when he replaced Ken Harvey, who retired.
O’Sullivan was an executive vice president at HSBC USA Inc. in
New York, before moving to HSBC Bank Canada as chief operating
officer and then in 2007 to London.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Howard Mustoe in London at 
 hmustoe@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
